                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 9.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of the Navy</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,
                        D. C.:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The British consul and the minister of war of the provisional government fear
                    seizure of two British steamers at Buenaventura to transport troops convoyed by
                    gunboat. Prevailed upon minister to dispatch gunboat, fearing possible
                    destruction British steamers. The landing <pb facs="0336" n="252"
                        xml:id="pg_252"/> of troops in the territory within the limit under my
                    control will cause prolonged campaign. Instructions from the Department are
                    requested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Diehl.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
